quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  70,40,"So I swear by the Lord of every East and every West, that We are indeed Able."
  70,41,"To replace them by those better than them; and none can escape from Us."
  70,42,"Therefore leave them, involved in their indecencies and play, till they confront their day which they are promised."
  70,43,"A day when they will come out of the graves in haste, as if rushing towards their goals."
  70,44,"With lowered eyes, disgrace overcoming them; this is the day, which they had been promised."
  71,1,"Indeed We sent Nooh towards his people saying that, “Warn your people before the painful punishment comes upon them.”"
  71,2,"He said, “O my people! I am indeed a Herald of clear warnings to you.”"
  71,3,"“That you must worship Allah and fear Him, and obey me.”"
  71,4,"“He will forgive you some of your sins, and give you respite up to an appointed term; indeed the promise of Allah cannot be averted when it arrives; if only you knew.”"
  71,5,"He said, “My Lord! I invited my people night and day.”"
  71,6,"“So for them, my calling them increased their fleeing away.”"
  71,7,"“And whenever I called them, so that You may forgive them, they always thrust their fingers into their ears, and covered themselves with their clothes, and remained stubborn and were extremely haughty.”"
  71,8,"“I then called them openly.”"
  71,9,"“Then I also told them publicly and also spoke to them softly in private.”"
  71,10,"“I therefore told them, ‘Seek forgiveness from your Lord; He is indeed Most Forgiving.’"
